edu.umaryland.igs.idea
Class ParameterExplanation

java.lang.Object
  edu.umaryland.igs.idea.ParameterExplanation

public class ParameterExplanation
extends Object

ParameterExplanation represents an explanation for users about the interpretation of a parameter. A ParameterExplanation can be converted to two different String formats, one suitable for GUI display and the other suitable for writing to a configuration file in .ctl format.

Constructor Detail

ParameterExplanation

public ParameterExplanation(String firstLine)
A ParameterExplanation is always created with only one line. After it is created, additional lines may be added.

Parameters:
firstLine - the first or only line of this parameter explanation
Method Detail

addLine

public void addLine(String additionalLine)
The addLine method adds a line to this parameter explanation. Lines are always added at the end.

Parameters:
additionalLine - the line to add to this parameter explanation

textRepresentation

public String textRepresentation()
This textRepresentation method returns a String representation of this parameter explanation suitable for writing to a .ctl file on the same line as a (name, value) pair.

Returns:
a String representation of this parameter explanation prefixed with the default prefix

textRepresentation

public String textRepresentation(String prefix)
This textRepresentation method returns a String representation of this parameter explanation suitable for writing to a .ctl file on its own line. Callers of this method specify the prefix argument based on the lengths of the names and values on the output set to ensure that the .ctl file is properly aligned.

Parameters:
prefix - the custom indentation prefix for this parameter explanation
Returns:
a String representation of this parameter explanation prefixed with the given prefix

graphicalRepresentation

public String graphicalRepresentation()
The graphicalRepresentation method returns a String representation of this parameter explanation suitable for display as a tool tip in the GUI. HTML breaks are used in place of newlines.

Returns:
a String representation of this parameter suitable for display as a tool tip in the GUI
